# prereqs: 
1. netcat (fullblown)
2. bash (fullblown, busybox ash didn't work for me. If can hack it 
   to work - send me a patch)
3. A box with gpios accessible via gpiolib

# instructions
1. Copy gpiohttpd.sh to the target box, edit the port at the top.
2. start it (root or any user, that can edit /sys/class/gpio)
3. navigate to http://boxip:8080 (or whatever port)
4. Play with it.

Page autoupdates every 5 seconds. Any change is committed via ajax
so you should see the result shortly. 

100% hacked in bash, css, javascript and html in under 500 lines of code. 
All in ONE file.

